{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775843818830,"sessionID":"ses_28777ef2bffePjp3TRYfubzpzd","part":{"id":"prt_d78883212001sFQsPneXvHnqpR","messageID":"msg_d78881d34001MCyph5v6LXAhPw","sessionID":"ses_28777ef2bffePjp3TRYfubzpzd","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_56598fc7e19d4b9d8f33ad88","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore agentcube project structure","prompt":"Explore the agentcube project at /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z to understand:\n1. The overall project structure (list top-level directories)\n2. Look for any existing picod related code in pkg/picod\n3. Look for any existing JWT or authentication related code\n4. Check if there are any existing spec files or delta-spec.md files\n5. Look at go.mod to understand dependencies\n\nReturn a comprehensive summary of what you find, including file paths and key code snippets if relevant.","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_28777bfc0ffeHb6x892vYik52y (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nHere is a comprehensive summary of the AgentCube project:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Overall Project Structure\n\n**Module:** `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube`\n**Go Version:** 1.25.0\n\n**Top-level directories (24 entries):**\n\n| Directory | Purpose |\n|-----------|---------|\n| `cmd/` | Entry points (contains `picod/main.go`) |\n| `pkg/` | Core library packages (6 sub-packages) |\n| `client-go/` | Kubernetes-style client library (informers, listers, clientset) |\n| `changes/` | Change requests AR-001 through AR-017 (each with proposal.md, design.md, tasks.md) |\n| `ci-cd/` | CI/CD design and spec |\n| `cli-toolkit/` | CLI toolkit design and spec |\n| `code-execution/` | Code execution design and spec |\n| `deployment/` | Deployment design and spec |\n| `idle-cleanup/` | Idle cleanup design and spec |\n| `integrations/` | Integration design and spec |\n| `python-sdk/` | Python SDK design and spec |\n| `sandbox-orchestration/` | Sandbox orchestration design and spec |\n| `session-routing/` | Session routing design and spec |\n| `session-store/` | Session store design and spec |\n| `testing/` | Testing-related files |\n\n**Top-level files:**\n- `go.mod`, `go.sum` -- Go module definition\n- `delta-spec.md` -- Main delta spec (AR-016: PicoD File Management API, 870 lines)\n- `design.md` -- Top-level design document\n- `proposal.md` -- Top-level proposal\n- `test_spec.md` -- Test specification\n- `.sdd_prompt.md` -- SDD prompt configuration\n- `coverage.out` -- Test coverage output\n\n---\n\n## 2. Existing PicoD Code in `pkg/picod`\n\nThe `pkg/picod` package is a fully implemented in-sandbox daemon for command execution and file management. It uses the **Gin** web framework.\n\n### File Structure:\n\n```\npkg/picod/\n  server.go          -- Server struct, route registration, health check\n  auth.go            -- AuthManager, JWT AuthMiddleware (RS256)\n  auth_test.go       -- Auth unit tests\n  config.go          -- Config struct and CLI flag parsing\n  config_test.go     -- Config tests\n  execute.go         -- Command execution handler\n  execute_test.go    -- Execute handler tests\n  files.go           -- Legacy file handlers (upload, list, download)\n  files.go (339 lines) -- Monolithic file operations\n  types.go           -- Shared types (ExecuteRequest/Response, FileInfo, etc.)\n  sanitize_test.go   -- Path sanitization tests\n  health_test.go     -- Health check tests\n  server_test.go     -- Server tests\n  files/             -- New structured file management subpackage (AR-016)\n    types.go         -- FileManager interface + all request/response types\n    manager.go       -- NewFileManager constructor\n    sanitize.go      -- Path sanitization logic\n    read.go          -- ReadFile handler\n    write.go         -- WriteFile handler\n    stat.go          -- StatFile handler\n    list.go          -- ListFiles handler\n    upload.go        -- UploadFile handler (with chunked support)\n    download.go      -- DownloadFile handler (with Range support)\n    delete.go        -- DeleteFile handler (batch support)\n    move.go          -- MoveFile handler\n    mkdir.go         -- MkDir handler\n    search.go        -- SearchFiles handler\n    chmod.go         -- Chmod handler\n    + corresponding _test.go files\n```\n\n### Key Code Snippets:\n\n**Server (`/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/server.go`):**\n```go\ntype Server struct {\n    engine       *gin.Engine\n    config       Config\n    authManager  *AuthManager\n    startTime    time.Time\n    workspaceDir string\n}\n\nfunc (s *Server) registerRoutes() {\n    api := s.engine.Group(\"/api\")\n    api.Use(s.authManager.AuthMiddleware())\n    {\n        api.POST(\"/execute\", s.ExecuteHandler)\n        api.POST(\"/files\", s.UploadFileHandler)\n        api.GET(\"/files\", s.ListFilesHandler)\n        api.GET(\"/files/*path\", s.DownloadFileHandler)\n    }\n    s.engine.GET(\"/health\", s.HealthCheckHandler)\n}\n```\n\n**Entry Point (`/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cmd/picod/main.go`):**\n```go\nfunc main() {\n    klog.InitFlags(nil)\n    config := picod.ParseFlags()\n    server := picod.NewServer(config)\n    if err := server.Run(); err != nil {\n        klog.Fatalf(\"server failed: %v\", err)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**FileManager Interface (`/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/files/types.go`):**\n```go\ntype FileManager interface {\n    ReadFile(ctx context.Context, req *ReadFileRequest) (*ReadFileResponse, error)\n    WriteFile(ctx context.Context, req *WriteFileRequest) (*WriteFileResponse, error)\n    StatFile(ctx context.Context, path string) (*StatFileResponse, error)\n    ListFiles(ctx context.Context, path string) (*ListFilesResponse, error)\n    UploadFile(ctx context.Context, req *UploadFileRequest) (*FileInfo, error)\n    UploadFileChunked(ctx context.Context, req *ChunkedUploadRequest) (*FileInfo, error)\n    DownloadFile(ctx context.Context, req *DownloadFileRequest) (*DownloadFileResponse, error)\n    DeleteFile(ctx context.Context, req *DeleteFileRequest) (*DeleteFileResponse, error)\n    MoveFile(ctx context.Context, req *MoveFileRequest) (*MoveFileResponse, error)\n    MkDir(ctx context.Context, req *MkDirRequest) (*MkDirResponse, error)\n    SearchFiles(ctx context.Context, req *SearchFilesRequest) (*SearchFilesResponse, error)\n    Chmod(ctx context.Context, req *ChmodRequest) (*ChmodResponse, error)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. Existing JWT / Authentication Code\n\nThere are **two** JWT authentication implementations in the project:\n\n### A. PicoD-side (verification only) -- `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n\nLocated at: `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/auth.go`\n\n```go\ntype AuthManager struct {\n    publicKey *rsa.PublicKey\n    mutex     sync.RWMutex\n}\n\nfunc (am *AuthManager) LoadPublicKeyFromEnv() error {\n    keyData := os.Getenv(PublicKeyEnvVar)  // \"PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\"\n    // ... PEM decode, x509.ParsePKIXPublicKey ...\n}\n\nfunc (am *AuthManager) AuthMiddleware() gin.HandlerFunc {\n    // Validates Authorization: Bearer <token>\n    // Uses jwt.Parse() with RS256, WithExpirationRequired(), WithIssuedAt(), WithLeeway(1min)\n    // Also wraps request body with http.MaxBytesReader (32MB limit)\n}\n```\n\nKey constants from `types.go`:\n```go\nconst (\n    PublicKeyEnvVar = \"PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\"\n    MaxBodySize     = 32 << 20  // 32MB\n)\n```\n\n### B. Router-side (signing + verification) -- `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n\nLocated at: `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/jwt.go`\n\n```go\ntype JWTManager struct {\n    privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey\n    publicKey  *rsa.PublicKey\n    clientset  kubernetes.Interface\n    config     *JWTConfig\n}\n\nfunc (m *JWTManager) GenerateToken(claims map[string]interface{}) (string, error) {\n    // Signs with RS256, includes exp, iat, iss claims\n}\n\nfunc (m *JWTManager) ParseAndValidateToken(tokenString string) (jwt.MapClaims, error) {\n    // Validates with RS256, checks issuer, handles expired/malformed tokens\n}\n\nfunc (m *JWTManager) TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx context.Context) error {\n    // Stores/loads RSA keypair from K8s Secret \"picod-router-identity\"\n}\n```\n\nConstants:\n```go\nconst (\n    rsaKeySize         = 2048\n    jwtExpiration      = 5 * time.Minute\n    IdentitySecretName = \"picod-router-identity\"\n)\n```\n\n### C. Router Auth Middleware -- `pkg/router/middleware.go`\n\nLocated at: `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/middleware.go`\n\n```go\nfunc AuthMiddleware(jwtManager *JWTManager) gin.HandlerFunc {\n    // Validates Bearer token via JWTManager.ParseAndValidateToken()\n    // Sets claims in gin context: c.Set(\"claims\", claims)\n}\n```\n\n### Authentication Flow:\n```\nClient --> Router (AuthMiddleware validates client JWT)\n         --> Router signs new JWT (RS256, 5min expiry)\n         --> PicoD (AuthMiddleware validates Router JWT via PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. Existing Spec Files and Delta-Spec Files\n\n### Root-level spec files:\n| File | Path |\n|------|------|\n| Main delta spec | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md` (AR-016, 870 lines) |\n| Test spec | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/test_spec.md` |\n\n### Per-change delta-spec files:\n| Change | Delta Spec Path |\n|--------|----------------|\n| AR-002 | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-002/delta-spec.md` |\n| AR-003 | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-003/delta-spec.md` |\n| AR-004 | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-004/delta-spec.md` |\n| AR-005 | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-005/delta-spec.md` |\n| AR-006 | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-006/delta-spec.md` |\n| AR-007 | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-007/delta-spec.md` |\n| AR-010 | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-010/delta-spec.md` |\n| AR-011 | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-011/delta-spec.md` |\n\n### Per-module spec files:\n| Module | Spec Path |\n|--------|-----------|\n| ci-cd | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/ci-cd/spec.md` |\n| cli-toolkit | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cli-toolkit/spec.md` |\n| code-execution | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/code-execution/spec.md` |\n| deployment | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/deployment/spec.md` |\n| idle-cleanup | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/idle-cleanup/spec.md` |\n| integrations | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/integrations/spec.md` |\n| python-sdk | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/python-sdk/spec.md` |\n| sandbox-orchestration | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/sandbox-orchestration/spec.md` |\n| session-routing | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/session-routing/spec.md` |\n| session-store | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/session-store/spec.md` |\n\n---\n\n## 5. Dependencies (go.mod)\n\n**Direct dependencies:**\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | v1.10.0 | HTTP web framework |\n| `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | v5.2.1 | JWT parsing and RS256 verification |\n| `github.com/google/uuid` | v1.6.0 | UUID generation (trace IDs) |\n| `github.com/prometheus/client_golang` | v1.22.0 | Metrics/prometheus |\n| `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | v9.18.0 | Redis client (session store) |\n| `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | v1.0.73 | Valkey client (session store) |\n| `github.com/alicebob/miniredis/v2` | v2.37.0 | Redis mock for testing |\n| `github.com/stretchr/testify` | v1.11.1 | Testing framework |\n| `k8s.io/api` | v0.34.1 | Kubernetes API types |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery` | v0.34.1 | Kubernetes apimachinery |\n| `k8s.io/client-go` | v0.34.1 | Kubernetes client |\n| `k8s.io/klog/v2` | v2.130.1 | Kubernetes logging |\n| `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | v0.22.2 | Kubernetes controller runtime |\n| `golang.org/x/net` | v0.51.0 | Networking utilities |\n\n**Notable indirect dependencies:** `golang.org/x/crypto` (v0.48.0), `golang.org/x/sys` (v0.41.0), `google.golang.org/protobuf` (v1.36.5)\n\n---\n\n## 6. pkg/ Package Summary\n\n| Package | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `pkg/picod/` | In-sandbox daemon: command execution + file management HTTP API |\n| `pkg/picod/files/` | Structured file management subpackage (11 operations) |\n| `pkg/router/` | API gateway/router: session management, load balancing, JWT auth, proxy |\n| `pkg/store/` | Session storage: Redis and Valkey backends with singleton pattern |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/` | Kubernetes workload management: reconciler, sandbox lifecycle handlers |\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/` | Custom Resource Definitions: AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter types |\n| `pkg/common/types/` | Shared type definitions |\n\n---\n\n## 7. Change Request History (AR-001 through AR-017)\n\nEach change request directory contains `proposal.md`, `design.md`, and `tasks.md`. Notable ones related to picod and auth:\n\n- **AR-011**: Router JWT signing and authentication (delta-spec.md exists)\n- **AR-015**: Original PicoD file management (monolithic `files.go`)\n- **AR-016**: PicoD file management API reorganization (main `delta-spec.md`, structured `files/` subpackage)\n- **AR-017**: PicoD JWT middleware (adds `auth.go` + `auth_test.go` to picod)\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_28777bfc0ffeHb6x892vYik52y","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube project structure","time":{"start":1775843688508,"end":1775843818827}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775843818918,"sessionID":"ses_28777ef2bffePjp3TRYfubzpzd","part":{"id":"prt_d788a3d4d0013RXI6ULmXfKc3h","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d78881d34001MCyph5v6LXAhPw","sessionID":"ses_28777ef2bffePjp3TRYfubzpzd","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":19564,"input":19235,"output":196,"reasoning":133,"cache":{"write":0,"read":0}},"cost":0.005852039}}
